    thinking: "**Analyzing Design Theme**\n\nI\'m currently breaking down the \"Bold Typography\" design theme. I\'ve pinpointed the key colors: a deep black `#0D0D0D` for the background, an off-white/beige `#E0D8D0` for text, and warm amber/gold accents `#C9A690`. Now, I need to consider how these colors can effectively create contrast and visual impact.\n\n\n**Integrating Bold Typography**\n\nI\'m now focusing on integrating the \"Bold Typography\" design into the app components. I\'m exploring a two-column layout with a dramatic chapter indicator and novel title on the left. The right column will hold the narrative with drop caps and mood tags. The plan is to include elegant serif fonts for headings and reading text, with tall sans-serif spacing.\n\n\n"
