    summary: "To set up a Vite React application with Capacitor for Android, you\'ll need to follow a series of steps to initialize your project, add Capacitor, configure it for Android, and then build and run your application. Capacitor acts as a bridge, allowing your web application (built with Vite and React) to run as a native mobile app and access device features[1][2].\n\nHere\'s a step-by-step guide:\n\n**1. Prerequisites**\nEnsure you have the following installed:\n*   Node.js (version 20+ is recommended) and npm[1][2].\n*   Android Studio with an Android SDK and emulator configured[1][3].\n*   A code editor like VS Code[1][2].\n\n**2. Create a Vite React Project**\nIf you don\'t have an existing Vite React project, create one using npm:\n\n\nSources:\n[1] [noqta.tn](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGRxkzKqcYTj5YYiQZD65iwIT-LHgd2MQGM3azD_ZMSsX2rJ_-Ytrydu3eKjZ8P41C7ERGSoWwzZYhtd9X6NO7NS-BlCDEf0fsJzJFLIiMOo3CIGgrU5xJhDMi5kKJch4T3Cty9ZOnAFrGY6E6p5yeuDOINmlWqT6BNHSP9Ypa9nvKkQg==)\n[2] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHXjVC2CNZZI414Pml5RwLzR_JYRjwIwcSNaaRjAZMEQ27KMIV0oP3F2takR1S_c-F58ghA7sVCNaM-qPFZo3JlQAA0GSRRS4Hga195SV1VTxhEYwCW1wurPKh6hxudCsF9y3t3END97sYl1U2SNz3753aceYJM0vcqeEoS5uWZIhBrCXCDYr9969I4c-jHTXek3CAuetebuXdJyeLT7iqCkQjQyvgTNaAUyUKL)\n[3] [staffordwilliams.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF2qjv3tI3otTqrs6pcEQIxsvwRorITbJDfZEMX8ak5sEMNHTPrZEfbeBCmGrcsNAlThL6wr0NOLLP4Ei1MPtbpgSIssJpngGCLcxiKoOz6bmH7v3zUtW8ktt0J8aQzhxO5ac49Xi5q4B-xgCBJeC3ZmNTpM3iF3lYCEb9n)\n[4] [otakit.app](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEJT0e5neVxmiAjHgmVgFkMpK30fwwWZjYJlASVFbda8112AADyfjfCGYHxTHJwMBr1BSvS3zYKlts9PgIDKIw1-YuvhAa2Ihm62CjAIt4j_jtNyd0mB69mzyUMk_GPVMwLvblEkOwNvXXcwVxrKPzcOIz0QQ_nguenqAHO)"
